To see API calls
Go to network tab - click Fetch/XHR

In request headers we have authorization token(upto 30 ..40 mts) called session token that will be used for subsequent calls.

Make a login call get the token 

authorization

API (Application programmng interface) acts as bridge between the client and the server.


Rules to be followed while creating API/services

Hit the endpoint/ call the API

Headers/cookies : 

Headers represent the meta-data associated with request and response.In layman terms, we are sending additional details to API to process our request.

Example : Authorization details.


API : micro services communicate using REST API calls 


POST/projectname/v2/cart/promo/add
